just_use dealer.go

# label: ELEGANT
# role: encodes domain knowledge

Dealer is autonomous: given a shuffled 104-card double deck, it builds the
board, deals two 15-card hands, and returns a GameSetup "photo" any client
(TS, Python, curl) can consume. Gopher can set up a game without a Cat
client in the loop.

Initial board is hard-coded (initialBoardDefs) — six stacks pulled from
deck 1 before dealing. Designer-chosen starting position, not random.
Parsed via the "KS", "TD" short labels so the designer intent stays
readable.
